        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 11:18PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 1118 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Camden, moving east at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Camden, Haigler Ridge, Nathan Bedford Forrest State Park,
Springville, Manleyville, Big Sandy, and Old Springville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for west
Tennessee.</instruction>
